<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98978826665007></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98978826665007><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=/item.html?item=2699&mid=98978826665007>RE: Haste explained</a> <a id=fs8 href=/item.html?item=2699&mid=98978826665007#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=20 width=20></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 13th 5:11 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It can also be defined as a percentage increase in the number of swings you make with your weapon per minute.  This tends to make more sense than an increase in damage.  Haste means you go faster or swing faster not damage more, although both the previous method and the method listed below both yeild the same result.<br><br>Weapon delay is basically calculated in tenths of a second.  So a delay of 16 would mean you were swinging your fist once every 1.6 seconds.  Now lets figure out how many times per minute you swing at this rate.<br><br>60/1.6=37.5 swings per minute<br><br>Now calculate the average swings you will make per minute with the 40% haste.<br><br>(100 + 40)/100 * 37.5 = 52.5 swings per minute<br><br>Now lets calculate what the average speed of your new hasted swing.<br><br>60/52.5 = 1.143 seconds(once again rounded up as above)<br><br>Now simply convert this back to tenths of a second and you have a average delay of 11.43. <br><br>So there are two methods of calculating haste, both of which yeild the same result.  That should put an end to any doubt anyone had I hope.<br><br>Powtro<br>34 Iksar Monk of Veeshan<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99229008061251></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99229008061251><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=/item.html?item=2699&mid=99229008061251>RE: Haste explained</a> <a id=fs8 href=/item.html?item=2699&mid=99229008061251#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=20 width=20></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=11556><span id= >Sylvain</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>20 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 11th 4:08 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Even easier formula (which yeilds 1% error)<br><br>Take weapons delay (say 16) and multiply it times the % of haste (say 40%) then add 1.<br><br>IE<br><br>9/16 wep<br><br>add 40% haste<br><br>16 x 40% = 6 (so subtract this from your delay)<br><br>16-6=10 (and now add the 1)<br><br>10+1=11<br><br>9/11 is new wep delay.<br><br>NOTE: the above math is more correct, BUT you cannot have a decimal in a delay of a wep so the 9/11.43 delay is false.<br>&nbsp;<br>******************<br>-Sylvain Feldwythe</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
